end on bootstrap output, creating a circular dependency. I might need to adjust the `compileClasspath` to avoid using `sourceSets.test.compileClasspath`. I'll explore alternatives to keep this organized.\\\\n\\\\n**Resolving nativeTest issues**\\\\n\\\\nI’m looking at the `nativeTest` configuration. It seems that `tasks.named(\\\\\\\"test\\\\\\\")` isn’t having any effect on `nativeTest`, and there's a circular dependency likely because `nativeTest` depends on some classes. This might complicate things since `nativeTest` compiles tests to native instead of running them in the JVM. I also wonder about dynamic access reports potentially using `javaTest`. I need to ensure there's no circular reference and might need to edit `build.gradle` for clarity on how `nativeTest` should incorporate `bootstrapProbeClasses`.\\\\n\\\\n**Inspecting build.gradle**\\\\n\\\\nI need to take a closer look at `build.gradle` along with the TCK plugin's native task configurations. It’s crucial to review relevant sections to understand how tasks are set up. This should help me identify any potential issues or conflicts that might be affecting the build process. By examining these configurations, I hope to figure out the best way to resolve any outstanding problems. Let’s delve into the specifics and see what we uncover!\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_053f396fbad82c020169f4dc7e3bd881939facda8066348d5d\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABp9NyKiKehgR-TZnvxdbbCcFFahDzimCxJhe_UxTHSLre_3J6wNWtA4_pxgrb-h7_1OjAPMG8YrxqXhWSGrFx7jZ1r4U3VoUCgrdqY2sT0j9Z8w9yuU-ZT09yM0fyzEzukBtk6s7-MCpLoFG-i1Q0I8F9q35vOBpJM9jsvq4fdyUhVKNGocckXDxIEuJNsWlUk31VqTZsgn0LlKJWl_HNQZ_AGs--LnYpKCRsvs7vSUQB0CzXV6Fxe13fSOLivOJUgK1lcjFPcXuIzuJmv7t_qiZpfNZHrcTOauX3DHmcRxRSVtZh_nGNh8Zdj0SbGM92ZWxcT6Sr2t47x5HDhmWe824N82N-vScybgudco4rWpAI5eTr5t9kchjXnVqFhQYcSZ9PCS9m4l1uZ04lx4A23T1C4oD9UC5MTasU6eNnq_BuzY3t0Tz14MH3fH5zdaD76bnzrPRFl4lFUF